The correspondent interviews a 150-year-old Caucasian grandfather.
He asks:
- Tell me, do you smoke?
Grandpa:
- Of course I smoke, two packs of cigarettes a day.
Reporter:
Tell me, do you drink?
Grandpa:
- Of course I drink, two bottles of vodka a day.
The correspondent is surprised:
- You are so many years old and you abuse bad habits so much ...
Grandfather:
- Otherwise I will never die at all!
